      <h2 id="special-thoughts-on-healing-after-losing-a-pet">Special Thoughts on Healing After Losing a Pet</h2>
      <p></p>
<p>Healing from the loss of a pet takes time, patience, and self-compassion.</p>
<p>Remember that grief is a process.  Allow yourself to feel your emotions fully without judgment.  Lean on your support system—friends, family, and even support groups—to share your memories and find comfort.  Cherish the time you spent with your beloved pet; their love will forever remain in your heart.  Take care of yourself—both physically and emotionally.  In time, the pain may lessen, and the beautiful memories will shine through.  May the love and memory of your pet bring you solace and peace.</p>
    
  
